Disappointing first experience. Stumbled on Which Wich when looking on Google maps for lunch spots near my office. I ordered online and got the Banh Mi, which looked awesome! Unfortunately we all know looks can be deceiving. First, no cilantro to be found on the sandwich at all (supposed to come with it). second the carrots are depreciated as being shredded and pickled...they were neither. Instead the carrots were large pieces of baby carrots, which just felt wrong. This ruins the texture and flavor of the sandwich. There was no Banh Mi flavor here, just jalapenos and bland, soggy pork. Maybe their more traditional sub sandwiches are better, but the Banh Mi was very disappointing.

This is one of the few times that I had a footlong sandwich and actually couldn't finish all of it. Made to order and really good at doing it, this is definitely where you grab a quick sandwich without sacrificing quality.

Ordered an egg salad sandwich at lunch time and got tuna fish instead. I'm allergic so could not eat it. Went back after work and the employee, Bedar told me I should have saved the tuna fish sandwich for 5-1/2 hours and returned it as there was nothing he could do. I threw out the sandwich and the receipt. So, it was over $10.00 for pop, chips and a sandwich and they refused to give me a new one. I made a special trip over there. I called their corporate headquarters as Bedar's attitude was extremely condescending and he told me a lot of people try to get free sandwiches (almost accusing me of being a criminal) and they told me because it was a franchise there was nothing they could do except contact the owner. The owner has not bothered to contact me. So, if they get your order wrong - beware - they will not try to fix it. I have also filed a complaint with the BBB mainly because of Bedar's attitude. Went back to give them another chance.  This time the girl toasted my sandwich INCLUDING the egg salad.  I asked her why she would think I wanted warm egg salad.  She replied they toast everything.  I got the manager who told her to redo the sandwich.  I was the only person in there at 12:30 p.m.  Gee, I wonder why.

Okay so I tried this place today for the first time. It was hot out, and I was in a rush, and tired from the heat. I had met up with some friends that I hadn't seen in a while. I, heaven forbid, forgot to mark one of the boxes because I didn't see it. This was around lunch time. The cashier threw a mini tantrum, saying "it'd be easier for me if people checked the boxes" because I forgot to check if I wanted my sandwich toasted or un-toasted. I was like, "really you crazy, I didn't see it and I've never been here before, calm down". I think someone else in his position should be hired in replacement of his ugly self. I know, I am sure he doesn't enjoy making sandwiches for a living, and taking peoples orders, but that is not my problem. It isn't a hard job, calm it down. Needless to say, I will never go back to that place. Maybe if they hire a friendlier staff, then sure.
